# GRASP — AI Assistant Rules

You are helping build Grasp — an AI learning agent.

Product: Upload any document, image, YouTube video or URL.
Get instant summary then chat with AI tutor about it.
Modes: Summary, Analysis, Q&A, Teaching, Flashcards.
Pricing: Free (3 uploads/month) / Pro £5/month unlimited.

Stack:
- Mobile: Expo / React Native
- Backend: FastAPI (Python)
- LLM Router: Claude Sonnet 4.6 (analysis, teaching) + Claude Haiku 4.5 (summary, Q&A) + Gemini 3 Flash (flashcards, images)
- Audio Transcription: OpenAI Whisper
- Embeddings: Azure OpenAI text-embedding-3-small
- Vector Store: Databricks Vector Search
- Storage: Azure Blob Storage
- Database: Azure SQL
- Auth: Google OAuth + JWT (access/refresh tokens)
- Payments: Stripe £5/month subscription
- Hosting: Azure Container Apps
- CI/CD: GitHub Actions

Rules:
- Always write complete files, never partial
- All secrets via environment variables — never hardcode API keys or connection strings
- Every function needs a docstring
- Modular structure always — business logic (auth/, agent/) stays separate from HTTP routing (api/routers/) and raw data access (api/services/)
- Every external call (LLM API, database, blob storage, third-party API) needs try/except error handling — never let unhandled exceptions reach the client
- Every mode/parser function returns a consistent dict shape including an "error" key when applicable
- When fixing bugs, explain why it broke before showing the fix
- Model IDs are defined as named constants, never hardcoded inline in multiple places
- Mobile first always
